03/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Seven suspected Kurdish rebels were killed while entering Turkish territory from Syria, local officials confirmed on Friday (April 1st). The alleged Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) members ignored gendarmerie's calls to surrender and opened fire. The incident happened near the town of Hassa in Hatay province. (Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, World Bulletin - 01/04/11)
